# Component Patterns

## Exports

- **Named exports** for reusable components
- **Default exports** only for `page.tsx` files

```typescript
// ✅ Reusable component
export function InfoCard({ title }: { title: string }) { ... }

// ✅ Page component
export default function QuizPage() { ... }
```

## Props Typing

- Inline destructured types for 1-2 simple props
- Separate `type` or `interface` for 3+ props

```typescript
// ✅ Simple props — inline
export function Badge({ label, color }: { label: string; color?: string }) { ... }

// ✅ Complex props — separate type
type SingleChoiceProps = {
  title: string;
  options: string[];
  onSelect: (value: string) => void;
  subtitle?: string;
};

export function SingleChoiceStep({ title, options, onSelect, subtitle }: SingleChoiceProps) { ... }
```

## Client Components

All components must include `"use client"` at the top (no server components in this codebase).

## Organization

Place components by feature:
- `components/quiz/` — Quiz-specific components
- `components/offer/` — Offer page components
- `components/ui/` — Reusable UI primitives

## Images

Use `next/image` with appropriate props:

```typescript
import Image from "next/image";

<Image
  src="/quiz/hero.png"
  alt="Description"
  fill
  className="object-cover"
  sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 520px"
  priority  // for above-the-fold images
/>
```

## Animations

Use CSS animation classes from `globals.css`:

```typescript
// ✅ Use existing classes
<div className="animate-fade-in-up">...</div>
<div className="animate-scale-in" style={{ animationDelay: "0.1s" }}>...</div>

// ❌ Don't use JS animation libraries
```
